This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with financial crime and predictive policing systems. It also uses random forest classifiers, which are commonly used in security-related applications. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses machine learning techniques to develop the White Collar Crime Early Warning System. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the societal issue of financial crime and its impact on individuals and institutions. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses identifying high-risk zones for financial crime, which could involve analyzing social and information networks. 

Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to develop a predictive model for financial crime.
